						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the Kēśava temple.</p>						

						<p>1223 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated the cyclic year Svabhānu, Āshāḍha śu. 13, Sōmavāra. Palaeographically the record may be assigned to the 13th century when the date would correspond to 1223 A.D., June 12, Monday.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift of oil from the oil-mill of the <hi rend="italic">satra</hi> for burning a perpetual lamp before a god by Chaṭeya-nāyaka.</p>						

						</summary>
